.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::LiveActivity \- NIP\-53 Live Activities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::LiveActivity;
\&
\&    # Live streaming event (kind 30311)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->live_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-stream\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqMy Stream\*(Aq,
\&        status     => \*(Aqlive\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Live chat message (kind 1311)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->chat_message(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        activity => "30311:$author_pk:$d_id",
\&        content  => \*(AqHello!\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Meeting space (kind 30312)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->meeting_space(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqmain\-room\*(Aq,
\&        room         => \*(AqMain Conference Hall\*(Aq,
\&        status       => \*(Aqopen\*(Aq,
\&        service      => \*(Aqhttps://meet.example.com/room\*(Aq,
\&        participants => [[$host_pk, \*(Aqwss://relay.com/\*(Aq, \*(AqHost\*(Aq]],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Meeting room event (kind 30313)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->meeting_room(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqannual\-meeting\*(Aq,
\&        space_ref  => ["30312:$space_pk:main\-room", \*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq],
\&        title      => \*(AqAnnual Meeting\*(Aq,
\&        starts     => \*(Aq1676262123\*(Aq,
\&        status     => \*(Aqplanned\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Room presence (kind 10312)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->room_presence(
\&        pubkey   => $hex_pubkey,
\&        activity => "30312:$space_pk:main\-room",
\&        hand     => \*(Aq1\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any live activity event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-53 (Live Activities). Five event kinds are used:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBLive Streaming Event\fR (kind 30311) \- An addressable event
advertising a live stream. Contains tags for title, summary, image,
streaming URL, recording URL, start/end times, status, participant
counts, hashtags, participant roles, relay lists, and pinned chat
messages. Updated continuously as participants join and leave.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBLive Chat Message\fR (kind 1311) \- A regular event for live
chat. MUST include an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag referencing the parent live activity.
MAY include an \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag for replies.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBMeeting Space\fR (kind 30312) \- An addressable event defining
a virtual interactive space. MUST have \f(CW\*(C`room\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`service\*(C'\fR,
and at least one \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag with a Host role.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBMeeting Room Event\fR (kind 30313) \- An addressable event
representing a scheduled or ongoing meeting. MUST reference a parent
space via \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag and have \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`starts\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBRoom Presence\fR (kind 10312) \- A replaceable event signaling
a user\*(Aqs presence in a room. Contains an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag with the room
reference and an optional \f(CW\*(C`hand\*(C'\fR tag for raised hand.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 4
\&    my $la = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-stream\*(Aq,
\&        status     => \*(Aqlive\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown
arguments. Array fields (\f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`participants\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`pinned\*(C'\fR) default to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS live_event
.IX Subsection "live_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->live_event(
\&        pubkey               => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        identifier           => $id,               # required (d tag)
\&        title                => $title,            # optional
\&        summary              => $summary,          # optional
\&        image                => $url,              # optional
\&        streaming            => $url,              # optional
\&        recording            => $url,              # optional
\&        starts               => $timestamp,        # optional
\&        ends                 => $timestamp,        # optional
\&        status               => $status,           # optional (planned/live/ended)
\&        current_participants => $count,            # optional
\&        total_participants   => $count,            # optional
\&        hashtags             => [$tag, ...],       # optional (t tags)
\&        participants         => [[$pk, $relay, $role, $proof], ...], # optional (p tags)
\&        relays               => [$url, ...],       # optional (relays tag)
\&        pinned               => [$event_id, ...],  # optional (pinned tags)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30311 live streaming Net::Nostr::Event. Each \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR
tag SHOULD have a displayable role name (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`Host\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`Speaker\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`Participant\*(C'\fR). The relay and proof fields in participant entries are
optional. Content defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS chat_message
.IX Subsection "chat_message"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->chat_message(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,                 # required
\&        activity   => "30311:$pk:$d_id",           # required (a tag)
\&        relay_hint => $relay_url,                  # optional
\&        reply_to   => $event_id,                   # optional (e tag)
\&        content    => $message,                    # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1311 live chat Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
references the parent live activity. When a relay hint is provided,
the \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag includes a \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR marker.
.SS meeting_space
.IX Subsection "meeting_space"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->meeting_space(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,               # required
\&        identifier   => $id,                       # required (d tag)
\&        room         => $name,                     # required (room tag)
\&        status       => $status,                   # required (open/private/closed)
\&        service      => $url,                      # required (service tag)
\&        participants => [[$pk, $relay, $role, $proof], ...], # required (p tags; $proof optional)
\&        summary      => $summary,                  # optional
\&        image        => $url,                      # optional
\&        endpoint     => $url,                      # optional
\&        hashtags     => [$tag, ...],               # optional (t tags)
\&        relays       => [$url, ...],               # optional (relays tag)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30312 meeting space Net::Nostr::Event. MUST have
at least one provider with a Host role. Status MUST be \f(CW\*(C`open\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`private\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`closed\*(C'\fR. Content defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS meeting_room
.IX Subsection "meeting_room"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->meeting_room(
\&        pubkey               => $hex_pubkey,       # required
\&        identifier           => $id,               # required (d tag)
\&        space_ref            => [$coord, $relay],   # required (a tag)
\&        title                => $title,            # required
\&        starts               => $timestamp,        # required
\&        status               => $status,           # required (planned/live/ended)
\&        summary              => $summary,          # optional
\&        image                => $url,              # optional
\&        ends                 => $timestamp,        # optional
\&        current_participants => $count,            # optional
\&        total_participants   => $count,            # optional
\&        participants         => [[$pk, $relay, $role], ...], # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30313 meeting room Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
references the parent meeting space. Content defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS room_presence
.IX Subsection "room_presence"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->room_presence(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,                 # required
\&        activity   => $room_a_tag,                 # required (a tag)
\&        relay_hint => $relay_url,                  # optional
\&        hand       => \*(Aq1\*(Aq,                         # optional (hand raised)
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 10312 room presence Net::Nostr::Event. This is a
replaceable event, so presence can only be indicated in one room at a
time. The \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag always includes a \f(CW\*(C`root\*(C'\fR marker. When no relay
hint is provided, the relay field defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $la = Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 30311, 1311, 30312, 30313, or 10312 event into a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\*(C'\fR object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized
kinds.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::LiveActivity\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-53 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 30311, 1311, 30312, 30313, or 10312
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30311 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 1311 missing \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30312 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`room\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`service\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 30313 missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`starts\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 10312 missing \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value (kinds 30311, 30312, 30313).
.SS title
.IX Subsection "title"
Event title (kinds 30311, 30313).
.SS summary
.IX Subsection "summary"
Event description.
.SS image
.IX Subsection "image"
Preview image URL.
.SS streaming
.IX Subsection "streaming"
Live stream URL (kind 30311).
.SS recording
.IX Subsection "recording"
Recording URL (kind 30311).
.SS starts
.IX Subsection "starts"
Start timestamp in seconds.
.SS ends
.IX Subsection "ends"
End timestamp in seconds.
.SS status
.IX Subsection "status"
Event status. For live events: \f(CW\*(C`planned\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`live\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`ended\*(C'\fR. For
meeting spaces: \f(CW\*(C`open\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`private\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`closed\*(C'\fR.
.SS current_participants
.IX Subsection "current_participants"
Current participant count string.
.SS total_participants
.IX Subsection "total_participants"
Total participant count string.
.SS hashtags
.IX Subsection "hashtags"
Arrayref of hashtag strings from \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS participants
.IX Subsection "participants"
Arrayref of arrayrefs from \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags. Each contains
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$pubkey, $relay, $role]\*(C'\fR and optionally a proof field.
Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS relays
.IX Subsection "relays"
Arrayref of relay URL strings from \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR tag. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS pinned
.IX Subsection "pinned"
Arrayref of pinned event IDs from \f(CW\*(C`pinned\*(C'\fR tags. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS activity
.IX Subsection "activity"
The \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag coordinate (kinds 1311, 10312).
.SS relay_hint
.IX Subsection "relay_hint"
Relay hint from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS reply_to
.IX Subsection "reply_to"
Parent event ID from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag (kind 1311).
.SS room
.IX Subsection "room"
Room display name from \f(CW\*(C`room\*(C'\fR tag (kind 30312).
.SS service
.IX Subsection "service"
Service URL from \f(CW\*(C`service\*(C'\fR tag (kind 30312).
.SS endpoint
.IX Subsection "endpoint"
API endpoint URL from \f(CW\*(C`endpoint\*(C'\fR tag (kind 30312).
.SS space_ref
.IX Subsection "space_ref"
Arrayref \f(CW\*(C`[$coord, $relay]\*(C'\fR from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag referencing parent space
(kind 30313).
.SS hand
.IX Subsection "hand"
Hand raised flag from \f(CW\*(C`hand\*(C'\fR tag (kind 10312).
